name: Air Fryer Chicken Strips
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Simple, basic air-fried chicken strips that are crunchy on the outside, tender on the inside, and packed full of flavor. Dip in ranch or your favorite dipping sauce.
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions
Combine flour, paprika, parsley, seasoned salt, and pepper in a large bowl
Beat egg in a separate bowl
Dredge each chicken strip first in the seasoned flour, then in beaten egg, then back in the seasoned flour
Place as many strips in the basket as you can without overcrowding
Lightly mist the tops of the strips with cooking spray
Flip strips over and lightly mist the tops with more cooking spray
